"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-celebrity-news-1932519-piers-morgan-paris-olympic-games-complaint\", \"text\": \"Piers Morganhas sparked backlash after he commented about Keely Hodgkinson winning gold at the 800m final. The middle distance runner won Team GB's first gold of theParis Olympics.  After the 22-year old sprinted to victory, Piers took to X to re-share an old tweet he posted in 2021 when Keely won silver during the Tokyo Olympics.  He originally wrote: \\\"I am sorry that facts make you vomit. Self-evidently, if you do not win a race, you lose it. And Keeley lost to someone the same age as her. But great to see her break the British record and I hope she now works even harder & wins Gold at Paris in 2024.\\\"  Following Keely's win, Piers then congratulated her and said: \\\" This aged well. Congrats@keelyhodgkinson- you took my advice and won,\\\" with added medal and clapping hands emojis.  Many of his followers have slammed the journalist in the comments section, with many describing him as \\\"shameful\\\" and told him to \\\"stop taking credit for her.\\\"  READ MORE:BBC's Jessica Ennis-Hill in tears as she makes heartbreaking family confession    One person said online: \\\"Will you stop claiming credit for every gold medal someone wins in the Olympics!\\\"  A second fan also wrote: \\\"Always making other people's success somehow about you. Shameless attention seeking.\\\"  A third person typed: \\\"Love that she won, but sometimes Piers you can be completely moronic.\\\" A fourth said: \\\"Your advice? Your ego is out of control.\\\"  After her sensational victory, Keely said: \\\"That was absolutely incredible. I have worked so hard over the last year and you could see how much it meant to me as I crossed the line. I can not believe I have finally done it. It means so much to me.  Do not miss:GMB's Kate Garraway halts show for 'breaking news announcement' about co-star  Do not miss:Emmerdale legend 'so proud' of co-star after 'tough days' on set  Do not miss:Coronation Street icon returns to cobbles after making dramatic exit  We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you. This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding. You can unsubscribe at any time. Read ourPrivacy Policy  This aged well. Congrats@keelyhodgkinson- you took my advice and won ?????? ????????????https://t.co/lDbaSBwMrn  \\\"And to do it here, where better? The audience was absolutely incredible, it felt like a home crowd to me. So I am super happy.  \\\"I feel like I have really grown over the last couple of years and this year is the year I have really tried to make that step up. The other girls are incredible. I knew to cross that line first I had to go one better than I ever had. I am just so pleased to do it today. The future is bright.  \\\"I have seen all the support from home, I have seen people messaging me and I have not got back to everyone yet but I will do and I have seen it all. It could not feel more amazing to that have support. I am super happy to bring it home for everyone. It's not just me, it's a whole team effort and they know who they are. This is our gold medal.\\\"    SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.  EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\"}"